rComments: Incredible teacher. I took phonetics around 5 times downtown but I didn't get it. It was 5 different profs teaching it and they all sucked. I got it the first time with her and because of her, I was able to finish my program with the other two courses required! I rank her as the FIRST prof I actually like and go back to.

The material is straightforward. The assignments are based straight from lecture notes which is posted in advance to the class. As long as you can do her practise midterms and finals which she provides, the exam will be a breeze.

No doubt the course material is tough, but this is a C level course afterall. I like how she is very organized and prepared for class. A great professor, and she replies to emails and answers your questions when you need her. GREAT PROF!!!

The book was kind of dry..I found it very difficult to stay awake during her lectures. She had a difficult time controlling the class and would have to stop every two mintues to make everyone shut up. At time we didnt get breaks which made the class even more difficult to sit through. Barely took any notes in the class.

The only prof I've ever come across with INCREDIBLY detailed class notes. I never took notes, only wrote down a couple of examples on the notes she posted. The class itself is a bore, but she's really helpful if you need it.
